Defendant Charles Edward Evans in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Charles Edward Evans in custody.   Thomas Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin, on behalf of Janet C Protasiewicz.

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state and defense counselt. 

Defendant sentenced to serve 1 YEAR at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION. Credit for 127 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 18 MONTHS.

Court orders defendant to serve 60 DAYS CONDITION TIME IN THE HOUSE OF CORRECTION to be utilized by Department of Corrections, Probation and Parole at their discretion.  
.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
-AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department;
-supervision under probation and parole mental unit;
-absolute sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs;
-no possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol;
-random urine screens;
-obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation;
-no contact with victim, UWM Police Officer Steven S or UWM Union Hall;
-pay restitution in the amount of $ZERO;
-provide DNA sample'
-pay MANDATORY DNA surcharge; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all applicable fees of supervision; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered.
-
-  Payment Plan for all monetary obligations to be established by Department of Corrections, Probation and Parole.  All unpaid balances at the end of the probationary period will convert to a civil judgment.
-  Firearm/Voting Rights/Civil Judgment Warning given.
-  No Cash Bail posted.

Appeal rights given. Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Copy given to defendant.
